The paper discusses a meta-learning method for improving few-shot learning, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method involves explicitly relating tasks on a graph, which suggests a focus on graph-based machine learning methods. The paper also mentions prototype-based classification, which is a common technique in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
